name: Diana Taurasi
summary: Diana Taurasi's remarkable Olympic career continues to make headlines. Despite being benched in the gold medal game, she remains a vital part of the USA Women's Basketball team. Her record-breaking sixth Olympic gold medal, achieved after the team's victory over France, is a testament to her longevity and dedication. While age may be catching up to her, Taurasi's Olympic legacy will endure. She has been a driving force behind Team USA's success and has inspired generations of basketball players. Her determination and leadership have earned her widespread respect and admiration, solidifying her place as an American icon in basketball.

name: 2028 Olympics
summary: The 2028 Los Angeles Olympics will have significant changes from the 2024 Paris Games. The venues will only be accessible by public transportation, and new sports like breaking and flag football will be added, while others like baseball and karate will be removed. The Olympics aim to be profitable, and organizers are exploring innovative technologies like flying taxis. Notable athletes like LeBron James and Stephen Curry are unlikely to participate, but Kevin Durant remains uncertain. Breaking's inclusion in the 2028 Games is still up for debate.

name: Matt Kuchar
summary: Golf professional Matt Kuchar made headlines for his unusual decision to end his round on the 72nd hole of the Wyndham Championship on Sunday, leaving him to complete it alone on Monday. Despite being close to finishing, Kuchar stopped play, citing his desire to set an example and uphold the integrity of the game. This bizarre move resulted in a unique solo-Monday finish, leaving him as the lone golfer competing. Kuchar's action garnered mixed reactions, with some praising his sportsmanship and others questioning his motives. Regardless, his decision to finish the tournament on his own terms ignited discussions about etiquette and the unwritten rules of golf.

summary: Legendary basketball player Sue Bird and soccer star Megan Rapinoe made waves as a prominent Olympic couple in Paris.
